cs.CV, cs.CL, cs.LG, cs.AI, cs.IR 

This paper is about image captioning, which involves computer vision (CV) and natural language processing (NLP). Therefore, cs.CV and cs.CL are the most likely sub-categories. The paper also proposes a new model that incorporates attention mechanisms, which is a common technique in machine learning (ML) and deep learning (DL), making cs.LG and cs.AI likely sub-categories as well. Finally, the paper evaluates its model on the MS-COCO dataset, which is a popular benchmark in computer vision and information retrieval (IR), making cs.IR a possible sub-category.
